  "original_title": "\u0da9\u0dd3\u0dc3\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dbd\u0dd3\u0da7\u0dbb\u0dca 4070 \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Diesel holds 4070 liters",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Matara headquarters police said that a fishing businessman from Weligama Mirissa area who was involved in smuggling petroleum mixed with diesel and selling it at a high price was arrested for questioning with a stock of 4070 liters of diesel.",
        "According to the information received by the intelligence officers of Galle Southern Naval Base, the police conducted this raid together with those officers.",
        "Police have seized 19 barrels of diesel, which are said to be mixed with petroleum, while they were on the jetty at Mirissa port.",
        "The businessman told the police that he had collected fuel for his multi-day cruises in this way.",
        "A senior police officer said that one of his vessels, who is the owner of three multi-day vessels, had gone to sea for work and another vessel was anchored at the fishing harbor and the other vessel was broken.",
        "The officer said that there were more than 2000 liters of diesel in the tank of the vessel which was anchored and no arrest was made because it was in the tank of the vessel.",
        "The police and navy intelligence officers have also received information that he has obtained and collected diesel in this way by using the dilapidated fishing vessel."
      ],
